  "privileged_info_summary": "The task uses real public Unsplash color photographs (IDs: photo-1549298916-b41d501d3772 at 5595x3997px and photo-1518837695005-2083093ee35b at 6000x4000px) as primary data source. The verification requires binary images with \u226595% pixels at pure black (\u226425) or pure white (\u2265230), <5% mid-tone pixels (80-175 range), balanced distribution (neither color >90%), and \u226575% pass score. Task timeout is 90 seconds with maximum 6 steps. A discrepancy exists in documentation: README.md line 89 claims gray range is 30-225, but verification checklist (line 112) and verifier.py specify 25-230. GIMP's threshold tool per documentation outputs pixels at extremes (0 or 255), making the \u00b125 tolerance reasonable for compression artifacts.",
